<br>
Great for dungeons.  Cast eye, sit, wander through to find mob, target mob, send pet in, pet kills, move up and loot.  Great to look around without dying.<br>
<br>
As mentioned above, it is great to pop the eye into walls to check out the world.  But this is even better.  When you go to camp the lava elemental in SolA for your Power of Fire [epic piece] you won't be able to get into the room because of the stupid drawbridge.  Here is how you get in there without any problem:<br>
  - pet guard where drawbridge comes down<br>
  - lev over to platform to the left of the drawbridge<br>
  - cast eye, which will pop into corridor.  the eye can opens doors and such...have it open the drawbridge.<br>
  - target nearest nasty little gnomes and send pet in to kill them<br>
  - when they are all dead simply pop the eye again and run in<br>
[note:  I'm a DE so the gnomes hate me.  This is much easier if you are not KOS to gnomes, then all you have to do is run in]<br>
<br>
Do the quest and get the item...you will love it.<br>
<br>
Casala, lv 54 Elementalist of Saryn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wrathen@themagicianstower>Wrathen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(1/15/03 7:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sorta port?</span><hr size=1> I will test this out the next time I am online but does anyone know offhand if you can take the eyes behind locked doors?<br>
